[{"_id":"a6bffe89-a37f-363a-9e6e-bb4cef5fb21d","authorName":"Lars","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"","message":"Hi Stephen,  \r\n\r\nI am using Code Contracts for my projects as well. One thing that I cannot get to work is the static checking when referencing the assembly (which has ccs defined) instead of referencing the project (which has ccs defined).  \r\n\r\nReferencing the project in Visual Studio only works for me (because I have the source code), but not everyone who might only get the assembly.  \r\n\r\nThe runtime checking works fine in both scenarios, but the static checking does not pick up the ccs. Have you had that issue?  \r\n\r\nLars","postId":"2011_01_simple-and-easy-code-contracts-47163d69-6fd5-3ec2-9c68-6459e398c3f9","replyTo":"","date":"2011-04-04T12:24:49Z","timestamp":1301919889,"authorUserId":""},{"_id":"62e83531-3f84-3493-b2e6-9ab7279f6230","authorName":"Stephen Cleary, Nito Programs","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"ad2250182ff26a84dda974e50cd94382","message":"@Lars:  \r\n\r\nSorry for the delayed reply!  \r\n\r\nI've tried the static checking against a runtime assembly (no project), and it works as I expect as long as that assembly has a CC assembly built as well (under Contracts\\MyLibrary.Contracts.dll, if memory serves correctly).  \r\n\r\nIf you're having a specific problem with CC, a good source for answers is the MS forum for CC. The MS CC team members are very active and respond quickly to bug and feature requests.","postId":"2011_01_simple-and-easy-code-contracts-47163d69-6fd5-3ec2-9c68-6459e398c3f9","replyTo":"","date":"2011-04-25T02:27:37Z","timestamp":1303698457,"authorUserId":""},{"_id":"e16a0ceb-a513-376c-b9e0-c5bd2870e733","authorName":"Şafak Gür","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"","message":"This comment has been removed by the author.","postId":"2011_01_simple-and-easy-code-contracts-47163d69-6fd5-3ec2-9c68-6459e398c3f9","replyTo":"","date":"2013-09-19T15:36:30Z","timestamp":1379604990,"authorUserId":""},{"_id":"f10f415b-c3a6-33f8-b033-24aaa2bd5391","authorName":"Ed Nafziger","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"a7b48232a536abb9eb8994a34f03cc5a","message":"Hi Stephen. I'm on the fence about starting to use Code Contracts, due to the fact it hasn't been updated for about 2 years. This article is almost 7 years old now. Do you still recommend using it? Thanks.","postId":"2011_01_simple-and-easy-code-contracts-47163d69-6fd5-3ec2-9c68-6459e398c3f9","replyTo":"","date":"2017-08-27T21:12:22Z","timestamp":1503868342,"authorUserId":"disqus:ednafziger"},{"_id":"4cbfdfce-2245-30aa-8513-bc28c61c87ce","authorName":"Stephen Cleary","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"ad2250182ff26a84dda974e50cd94382","message":"I really don't use it anymore at all.\r\n\r\nIt's a shame, because CC was a great project and very helpful, and I think it had a ton of potential. But it was never properly updated for async code, and it's been all but abandoned now.","postId":"2011_01_simple-and-easy-code-contracts-47163d69-6fd5-3ec2-9c68-6459e398c3f9","replyTo":"f10f415b-c3a6-33f8-b033-24aaa2bd5391","date":"2017-08-28T15:08:05Z","timestamp":1503932885,"authorUserId":"disqus:stephen_cleary"},{"_id":"6b409ba7-b8f7-3058-b990-497ce5482ad3","authorName":"Stephen Cleary","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"ad2250182ff26a84dda974e50cd94382","message":"No. You can get part of the way with Roslyn analyzers, and the next major version of C# has nullable reference types, which will get us a lot more of the way. But there's no deep static analysis or invariants or anything like that.","postId":"2011_01_simple-and-easy-code-contracts-47163d69-6fd5-3ec2-9c68-6459e398c3f9","replyTo":"ec37fb2c-04c3-3853-8171-20edac56f0ff","date":"2018-05-20T19:52:26Z","timestamp":1526845946,"authorUserId":"disqus:stephen_cleary"},{"_id":"ab9355e0-d4c3-34dc-aeb9-2f1cb4c6bd9a","authorName":"Collin Stevens","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"9f8f725a01bd3acaa59c2cb39748f468","message":"Yeah, I'm not able to move my company to the next language version and/or .NET framework so easily without a lot of red tape, unfortunately.","postId":"2011_01_simple-and-easy-code-contracts-47163d69-6fd5-3ec2-9c68-6459e398c3f9","replyTo":"6b409ba7-b8f7-3058-b990-497ce5482ad3","date":"2018-05-20T22:03:19Z","timestamp":1526853799,"authorUserId":"disqus:disqus_Am4h1TMioB"},{"_id":"ec37fb2c-04c3-3853-8171-20edac56f0ff","authorName":"Collin Stevens","authorEmailEncrypted":"","authorEmailMD5":"9f8f725a01bd3acaa59c2cb39748f468","message":"Did you manage to find a suitable replacement?","postId":"2011_01_simple-and-easy-code-contracts-47163d69-6fd5-3ec2-9c68-6459e398c3f9","replyTo":"4cbfdfce-2245-30aa-8513-bc28c61c87ce","date":"2018-05-20T07:42:55Z","timestamp":1526802175,"authorUserId":"disqus:disqus_Am4h1TMioB"}]